TITLE: Configuring ZPA Provider with Private Key Authentication
DESCRIPTION: Example configuration for the ZPA Terraform provider using OneAPI private key authentication method. Requires client_id, private_key, vanity_domain, zscaler_cloud and zpa_customer_id.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zscaler/terraform-provider-zpa/blob/master/docs/index.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
terraform {
    required_providers {
        zpa = {
            version = "~> 4.0.0"
            source = "zscaler/zpa"
        }
    }
}

provider "zpa" {
  client_id     = "[ZSCALER_CLIENT_ID]"
  private_key   = "[ZSCALER_PRIVATE_KEY]"
  vanity_domain = "[ZSCALER_VANITY_DOMAIN]"
  zscaler_cloud = "[ZSCALER_CLOUD]"
  zpa_customer_id = "[ZPA_CUSTOMER_ID]"
}
```

