TITLE: Creating a ZPA Policy Access Rule with SCIM Attributes in Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to define a ZPA policy access rule with SCIM attribute header conditions. It retrieves SCIM attributes for a user's given name and family name, then creates a rule that allows access when these attributes match specified values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zscaler/terraform-provider-zpa/blob/master/docs/resources/zpa_policy_access_rule_scim_attribute.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: terraform
CODE:
```
data "zpa_scim_attribute_header" "givenName" {
  name     = "name.givenName"
  idp_name = "IdP_Name"
}

data "zpa_scim_attribute_header" "familyName" {
  name     = "name.familyName"
  idp_name = "IdP_Name"
}

resource "zpa_policy_access_rule" "this" {
  name                          = "Example"
  description                   = "Example"
  action                        = "ALLOW"
  operator                      = "AND"

  conditions {
    operator = "OR"
    operands {
      object_type = "SCIM"
      idp_id      = data.zpa_scim_attribute_header.givenName.idp_id
      lhs         = data.zpa_scim_attribute_header.givenName.id
      rhs         = "John"
    }
    operands {
      object_type = "SCIM"
      idp_id      = data.zpa_scim_attribute_header.familyName.idp_id
      lhs         = data.zpa_scim_attribute_header.familyName.id
      rhs         = "Smith"
    }
  }
}
```

