TITLE: Configuring ZPA Application Segment with Lowercase Domain Names
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform resource block creates a ZPA application segment, using the 'lower' function to ensure all domain names are in lowercase to prevent configuration drifts.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zscaler/terraform-provider-zpa/blob/master/docs/guides/troubleshooting.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: terraform
CODE:
```
resource "zpa_application_segment" "this" {
  name              = var.name
  description       = var.description
  enabled           = var.enabled
  health_reporting  = var.health_reporting
  bypass_type       = var.bypass_type
  is_cname_enabled  = var.is_cname_enabled
  tcp_port_range    = var.tcp_port_ranges
  udp_port_range    = var.udp_port_ranges
  domain_names      = [for names in var.domain_names : lower(names)]
  segment_group_id  = var.segment_group_id
  tcp_keep_alive    = var.tcp_keep_alive
  icmp_access_type  = var.icmp_access_type
  server_groups {
    id = var.server_groups
  }
}
```

