TITLE: Creating a Client Isolation Access Rule in ZPA
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform configuration creates a basic isolation policy rule that enforces isolation for web browser client types. It references an isolation profile data source and sets appropriate conditions for the policy rule.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zscaler/terraform-provider-zpa/blob/master/docs/resources/zpa_policy_isolation_rule.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: terraform
CODE:
```
# Get Isolation Profile ID
data "zpa_isolation_profile" "isolation_profile" {
    name = "zpa_isolation_profile"
}

#Create Client Isolation Access Rule
resource "zpa_policy_isolation_rule" "this" {
  name                          = "Example_Isolation_Policy"
  description                   = "Example_Isolation_Policy"
  action                        = "ISOLATE"
  operator = "AND"
  zpn_isolation_profile_id = data.zpa_isolation_profile.isolation_profile.id

  conditions {
    operator = "OR"
    operands {
      object_type = "CLIENT_TYPE"
      lhs = "id"
      rhs = "zpn_client_type_exporter"
    }
  }
}
```

