TITLE: Running Terraform Initialization, Planning, and Apply - Shell (Bash)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet provides the sequence of Terraform CLI commands (init, plan, apply) required to set up the infrastructure as defined in the current working directory. The commands initialize the backend and provider plugins, generate an execution plan, and apply the changes to deploy resources. Requires Terraform CLI installed and a configured ZPA provider. Takes no parameters directly, operates on local configuration files, and outputs formatted status to terminal.
